If you've got solar panels and an EV, you're sitting on a goldmine of free motoring — but only if your charger can actually make use of that solar energy. The myenergi Zappi and Ohme Home Pro are the two most popular smart chargers in the UK, and both support solar integration. But they approach it very differently.

The Zappi was built from the ground up for solar diversion. The Ohme was built for smart tariff optimisation, with solar bolted on. That fundamental difference shapes everything — and makes the choice between them more nuanced than you'd expect.

